    '- Government-wide result: $1.24B awarded = 6.11% of eligible contract value',
    '- Year-over-year: ~$400M LESS than prior year in actual dollars (percentage up, dollars down)',
    '- Deputy Head exceptions nearly doubled: $7.5B → $14.7B in a single year',
    '- DND accounted for 87.7% of all exceptions',
    '- Source: ISC Mandatory Minimum 5% Target Results, FY 2023–24',
    '',
    'PSIB — PROCUREMENT STRATEGY FOR INDIGENOUS BUSINESS',
    '- In effect since 1996',
    '- A mandatory federal procurement policy — not a diversity initiative',
    '- Set-Aside Program: Contracts reserved exclusively for Indigenous businesses',
    '- Mandatory set-aside triggers: (1) Geographic area where Indigenous people ≥ 51% of population; OR (2) Indigenous people are primary recipients of the good/service/construction',
    '- All other procurements: Must consider set-aside and document decision either way',
    '- 33% Indigenous content rule: On set-aside contracts, winning business must perform ≥ 33% of contract value itself or through qualified Indigenous subcontractors — must be written into RFP evaluation criteria AND contract terms — cannot be added after award',
    '- IBD verification: Must happen at contract award, not RFP stage',
    '- IPP (Indigenous Participation Plan): For large/complex procurements — prime contractor commits to a defined % to Indigenous subcontractors. Counts toward 5% target. Must be monitored post-award.',
    '',
    'INDIGENOUS BUSINESS DIRECTORY (IBD)',
    '- ~3,000 businesses currently listed (exact count fluctuates)',
    '- 51% Indigenous ownership and control required for registration',
    '- 2023: ISC took direct responsibility for assessments — tighter, more consistent standards',
    '- October 2024: Comprehensive integrity review launched — businesses that did not meet criteria were removed',
    '- IBD is publicly searchable online, maintained by ISC',
    '',
    'MODERN TREATIES',
    '- 25 Modern Treaties currently in effect across Canada',
    '- 22 contain economic measures with specific procurement obligations legally binding on the Crown',
    '- Not policy — constitutionally protected signed agreements; cannot be overridden by policy change or Deputy Head exception',
    '- PSIB and Modern Treaty obligations operate in parallel — must check both',
    '',
    'TIPS — TRANSFORMATIVE INDIGENOUS PROCUREMENT STRATEGY',
    '- Active 5-year co-development process launched 2021 by ISC',
    '- Not completed policy — ongoing. Co-development table formed April 2024 with 40+ federal and Indigenous members',
    '- MMF and CANDO nominated as co-chairs in 2025',
    '',
    'MAY 2025 PSIB COMPLIANCE AUDIT',
    '- Completed: May 2025 by Indigenous Services Canada (internal — not third-party)',
    '- Coverage period: April 1, 2022 to March 31, 2024',
    '- Confirmed strengths: Strong governance framework, clear alignment with 5% target, sound accountability structure',
    '- Identified gaps: Need for finalized standardized procedures and comprehensive checklists for complex cases; exception documentation practices under increasing scrutiny',
    '',
    '== NACIA FORGE SERVICES ==',
    '',
    'TIPS READINESS DIAGNOSTIC',
    '- Price: $2,000–$3,000 (depending on organizational size and scope)',
    '- Timeline: 2–3 weeks',
    '- Output: Written findings document + prioritized roadmap',
    '- Four pillars: (1) Governance & Policy Alignment (2) Procurement Systems & Processes (3) Indigenous Supplier Strategy (4) Risk, Reporting & Data Readiness',
    '- This is Phase 1 of the four-phase roadmap — the starting point',
    '',
    'COMPLIANCE AUDIT & PROCUREMENT ANALYSIS',
    '- Custom scope — Phase 2, follows the Diagnostic',
    '',
    'WORKSHOPS',
    '- Launchpad: Teams new to PSIB',
    '- Accelerator: Teams with experience, operationalizing PSIB systems',
    '- Mastery: Organizations committed to high-performance Indigenous procurement',
    '',
    'BOOKING LINK: https://cal.com/nacia-forge/30min-compliant-assessment',
    '',
    '== BEHAVIOUR RULES ==',
    '',
    '1. Never use these words: leverage, utilize, facilitate, synergy, transformative, revolutionary, game-changer, cutting-edge, seamlessly, robust, empower, unlock, harness, tapestry, realm, landscape.',
    '2. Never round or approximate numbers — use exact figures as stated above. Use ~ only for IBD count.',
    '3. Never conflate PSIB (policy) with Modern Treaties (law). They operate in parallel.',
    '4. Never overstate what sources say. The May 2025 audit "identified a need for" standardized procedures — it did not say departments are non-compliant.',
    '5. Keep answers concise and direct. No padding. No bullet-point lists unless the question genuinely requires enumeration.',
    '6. When a visitor signals readiness to take action, or asks how to get started, or asks about pricing and next steps — provide the booking link naturally: https://cal.com/nacia-forge/30min-compliant-assessment',
    '7. Do not push the booking link on every message. Read the conversation. Offer it once when the moment is right.',
    '8. You are not a lawyer or auditor. For legal determinations, recommend the visitor speak with legal counsel.',
    '9. If asked something outside your knowledge base, say so plainly and offer to connect them via the booking link.',
    '10. Format your responses in plain HTML — wrap paragraphs in <p> tags. For the booking link use: <a href="https://cal.com/nacia-forge/30min-compliant-assessment" target="_blank" rel="noopener">book a 30-minute assessment</a>'
  ].join('\n');

  /* ── STATE ── */
  var history  = [];
  var isOpen   = false;
  var isTyping = false;
  var greeted  = false;

  /* ── DOM refs ── */
  var trigger  = document.getElementById('nf-bot-trigger');
  var window_  = document.getElementById('nf-bot-window');
  var messages = document.getElementById('nf-bot-messages');
  var input    = document.getElementById('nf-bot-input');
  var sendBtn  = document.getElementById('nf-bot-send');

  if (!trigger || !window_ || !messages || !input || !sendBtn) return;

  /* ── TOGGLE ── */
  trigger.addEventListener('click', function () {
    isOpen = !isOpen;
    trigger.classList.toggle('nf-open', isOpen);
    window_.classList.toggle('nf-open', isOpen);

    if (isOpen) {
      input.focus();
      if (!greeted) {
        greeted = true;
        setTimeout(function () {
          addMessage('bot',
            '<p>Bonjour. Je suis ici pour répondre à vos questions sur la cible obligatoire de 5 % en matière d\'approvisionnement autochtone au Canada, le SEAA, le RFE, les obligations découlant des traités modernes, et la façon dont Nacia Forge peut aider votre organisation à se préparer.</p>' +
            '<p>Que souhaitez-vous savoir ?</p>'
          );
        }, 300);
      }
    }
  });

  /* ── ADD MESSAGE TO UI ── */
  function addMessage (role, html) {
    var div = document.createElement('div');
    div.className = 'nf-msg nf-' + role;

    var bubble = document.createElement('div');
    bubble.className = 'nf-msg-bubble';
    bubble.innerHTML = html;

    div.appendChild(bubble);
    messages.appendChild(div);
    messages.scrollTop = messages.scrollHeight;
    return div;
  }

  /* ── TYPING INDICATOR ── */
  function showTyping () {
    var div = document.createElement('div');
    div.className = 'nf-msg nf-bot';
    div.id = 'nf-typing-indicator';

    var indicator = document.createElement('div');
    indicator.className = 'nf-typing';
    indicator.innerHTML = '<span></span><span></span><span></span>';

    div.appendChild(indicator);
    messages.appendChild(div);
    messages.scrollTop = messages.scrollHeight;
  }

  function hideTyping () {
    var el = document.getElementById('nf-typing-indicator');
    if (el) el.parentNode.removeChild(el);
  }

  /* ── SEND MESSAGE ── */
  function send () {
    var text = input.value.trim();
    if (!text || isTyping) return;

    input.value = '';
    input.style.height = 'auto';
    addMessage('user', '<p>' + escapeHtml(text) + '</p>');

    history.push({ role: 'user', content: text });
    isTyping = true;
    sendBtn.disabled = true;
    showTyping();

    /* ── TODO: CORS PROXY REQUIRED ─────────────────────────────────────────────
       Cloudflare Pages is a static host — browsers cannot call api.anthropic.com
       directly due to CORS. You need a thin proxy. Two options:
       A) Cloudflare Worker (free, <20 lines) — recommended. Deploy a Worker at
          /api/chat on the same domain that forwards to Anthropic and adds your key.
       B) Point this fetch at your existing Render Flask service by adding a
          /api/chat route that proxies the Anthropic call.
       Update PROXY_URL below once your proxy is live.
    ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    var PROXY_URL = '/api/chat'; /* ← your Cloudflare Worker or Render proxy endpoint */

    fetch(PROXY_URL, {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }, /* proxy adds x-api-key */
      body: JSON.stringify({
        model: 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514',
        max_tokens: 1000,
        system: SYSTEM_PROMPT,
        messages: history
      })
    })
    .then(function (res) { return res.json(); })
    .then(function (data) {
      hideTyping();
      isTyping = false;
      sendBtn.disabled = false;

      var reply = '';
      if (data && data.content && data.content[0] && data.content[0].text) {
        reply = data.content[0].text;
      } else {
        reply = '<p>Something went wrong on my end. Please try again or <a href="https://cal.com/nacia-forge/30min-compliant-assessment" target="_blank" rel="noopener">book a call directly</a>.</p>';
      }

      addMessage('bot', reply);
      history.push({ role: 'assistant', content: reply });
    })
    .catch(function () {
      hideTyping();
      isTyping = false;
      sendBtn.disabled = false;
      addMessage('bot', '<p>I\'m having trouble connecting right now. You can <a href="https://cal.com/nacia-forge/30min-risk-assessment" target="_blank" rel="noopener">book a call directly</a> and we\'ll get you answers.</p>');
    });
  }

  /* ── SEND BUTTON ── */
  sendBtn.addEventListener('click', send);

  /* ── ENTER TO SEND (shift+enter for newline) ── */
  input.addEventListener('keydown', function (e) {
    if (e.key === 'Enter' && !e.shiftKey) {
      e.preventDefault();
      send();
    }
  });

  /* ── AUTO-RESIZE TEXTAREA ── */
  input.addEventListener('input', function () {
    this.style.height = 'auto';
    this.style.height = Math.min(this.scrollHeight, 100) + 'px';
  });

  /* ── ESCAPE HTML ── */
  function escapeHtml (str) {
    return str
      .replace(/&/g, '&amp;')
      .replace(/</g, '&lt;')
      .replace(/>/g, '&gt;')
      .replace(/"/g, '&quot;');
  }

})();
</script>

